subject: PLDM: Implement host-condition interface
commitMessage:
PLDM: Implement host-condition interface

This commit implements the PDI interface defined at
https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc
/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/42435

pldmd hosts the new xyz.openbmc_project.Condition.HostFirmware interface
so it's difficult for it to have other code within pldmd to also set
this during startup.

The solution proposed in this commit is to provide the hostPDRHandler
object to the HostFirmware interface implementation. This then allows
reads of the HostFirmware property to just ask the hostPDRHandler for
the current state of the host.

Signed-off-by: Pavithra Barithaya <pavithra.b@ibm.com>
Change-Id: I3f7d4f573332e96fcd3ae594dc25750070cd6e62

This review comment doesn't make much sense to me. The whole point of this commit is to implement https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/master/xyz/openbmc_project/Condition/HostFirmware.interface.yaml within PLDM service. This is needed so phosphor-state-manager service code can look for this interface and call it to determine if host is up.
since these changes are related to MEX story, it may take sometime to merge. We can take up another story to make changes to that once we merge this.
